*****Exercise 11. The converse of Theorem 66 is the following:

Vy. Ex. F(x, y) |- Ex. Vy. F(x, y) Wrong!

Vy. Ex. F(x, y)---------Vx. (1=y v 2=y)
						(1=1 v 2=1) ^(1=2 v 2=2)
						(T v F) ^(F v T)
						(T ^ T)
							T

Ex. Vy. F(x, y)--------Ex. (x=1 ^ x=2)
						(1=1 ^ 1=2) v (2=1 ^ 2=2)
						(T ^ F) v (F ^ T)
						(F v F)
							F



